description: Forbidden orchestration habits — overlapping writes, skipped shapers, unverified summaries
alwaysApply: true
---

# Anti-patterns — do not do these

- Spawning agents that all edit the same files without worktree isolation (`best-of-n-runner`). They will stomp on each other.
- Skipping the shaper because "I know what I want." If you knew, the brief would already exist. Write it.
- Producing content artifacts (series plans, post drafts, indexes) without the shaper because "I know the material." Knowing the topic is not a scoped brief.
- Treating subagent summaries as ground truth without reading the diff.
- Writing memory for things derivable from the repo (file paths, conventions, architecture).
- Adding memory entries faster than removing stale ones. The index must stay clean.
- Sequential `Task` dispatch of independent work. Parallel or it's wasted wall-clock.
- Letting reviewer agents become optional. The gate is the gate.
